---
import SiteLayout from "../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="The terms under which you may use PoE2 Hub."
>
  <h1>Terms of Service</h1>

  <p class="updated-note">Last updated: July 15, 2026</p>

  <h2>Acceptance of terms</h2>
  <p>
    By accessing PoE2 Hub at <a href="https://poe2hub.net">https://poe2hub.net</a>
    you agree to these terms. If you do not agree, please do not use the site.
  </p>

  <h2>Nature of the content</h2>
  <p>
    This site publishes guides, reference material, and opinion about
    Path of Exile 2. Content is provided for information purposes only. Game
    mechanics and values change with patches; while we verify data
    against multiple sources and label the applicable game version, we
    cannot guarantee that every value remains accurate after a game
    update.
  </p>

  <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
  <p>
    Original text, page structure, and interactive tools on this site are
    the property of PoE2 Hub. Path of Exile 2, game assets, and related
    trademarks are the property of Grinding Gear Games. This site is
    an independent fan resource and claims no ownership of the underlying
    game.
  </p>

  <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
  <p>
    You may not use this site to attempt unauthorized access to our
    infrastructure, scrape content at scale for republication, or
    misrepresent our content as your own.
  </p>

  <h2>Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
  <p>
    The site is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind. We do
    not warrant that the site will be uninterrupted or error-free.
  </p>

  <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the maximum extent permitted by law, PoE2 Hub shall not be
    liable for any indirect or consequential damages arising from the use
    of this site.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We may revise these terms at any time. Continued use of the site
    after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about these terms can be sent to
    <a href="mailto:contact@poe2hub.net">contact@poe2hub.net</a>.
  </p>
</SiteLayout>

<style>
  .updated-note { color: var(--text-faint); font-size: 0.88rem; }
  h2 { margin-top: var(--space-3); }
  p { color: var(--text-dim); line-height: 1.75; }
</style>
